<item>
            <title>[LU-12291] Wrong NI selection on asymmetric Multi-rail environment</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12291</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the sending node is MultiRail and the receiving node is non-MultiRail,&lt;br/&gt;
the sending node use always the same NI (even if the sending NI is blocken, the blocken NI is used).&lt;br/&gt;
This may be the specification of MultiRail, but blocken device should be used.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    REMOTE  IB0              (non-MultiRail node)
            &#8593;
            x
            |
     LOCAL  IB0      IB1     &amp;lt;- always use IB0(not in round-robin fashion)
            failure    
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the receiving node is non-MultiRail, we check whether its device is normal or out of service and reset the device in case of failure.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="55619">LU-12291</key>
            <summary>Wrong NI selection on asymmetric Multi-rail environment</summary>
